:: February 2000 {"position":"700,550","size":"100,100"}
You continue to attend meetings about the new accounting system, and eventually the CFO believes that you made the right decision about building automated controls.  

In February, you observe that Enron only requires one signer for checks.  You remember when you studied for the CIA exam that having dual signatures will reduce the chances of fraud.  You approach the CFO and she said that dual signatures will create inefficiencies.  You recommend:

[[Implementing Dual Signatures]] 

[[Sticking with Single Signatures]] 


:: Implement a Credit Card Policy {"position":"500,700","size":"100,100"}
This answer is correct.  Implementing a credit card policy will allow for rules surrounding company credit cards to be in writing which will make it easier to enforce.  It will also help reduce waste.

[[April 2000]]


:: Implement an Internet Usage Policy {"position":"500,1300","size":"100,100"}
