:: Start of Game {"position":"700,250","size":"100,100"}
It is January 1, 2000.  Your computer and every computer in the country survived Y2K.  Before the holidays, in addition to preparing for Y2K, upper management asked you to look the other way when it comes to policies and procedures.  

You are the Director of Internal Audit at the Enron Corporation which is an energy company based out of Houston, Texas with 20,600 employees.  The company is doing so well that they bought naming rights to the new Houston Astros stadium.    

You are a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) and a Certified Internal Auditor (CIA).  You are bound by both the AICPA and IIA's Code of Ethics and you want to do the right thing.  You will be faced with important decisions within the next year. [[January 2000]]



